Montpellier H rault Sport Club announces the signing of Bafana Bafana star Keagan Dolly. Keagan Dolly who struggled to move away from former club, reigning African Champions Mamelodi Sundowns due to contractual issues.However the determined French Ligue 1 side Montpellier activated his R25 million buyout clause with a 1.7 million euros fee.French reports reveal that Keagan Dolly signed a 4 year contract with the French side with the 2012 French champions Montpellier confirming it on twitter.RELATED: PSL done deals in January Transfer Window Translated to English the tweet reads: &#8220;Welcome home Keagan Dolly . We wish you the best&#8217;